KUWAIT CITY: Ahmadi police in Kuwait discovered the body of a child who had been missing for a few days, according to the Interior Ministry. Investigations revealed that he was murdered by a family member. Police were able to locate the crime scene after conducting intensive investigations and discovered that the suspect had murdered and buried the child, according to a statement released by the ministry on Sunday. The suspect is in police custody and will face legal proceedings as the case is still under investigation, the ministry added.